  <h2>Your vimrc</h2>
      <p>This is a special file that will allow you to customize your vim experience. For example, you can define how many spaces are in a tab, make line numbers show, etc. To open it navigate to your home directory in terminal cd ~ and vim open your .vimrc file (vim .vimrc)</p>
